  "texts": [
    "They also reveal how position information varies with other field properties over theta phases (Supplementary Fig. 5I, J).",
    "For example, information is negatively correlated with field width, confirming the interpretation that more informative phases have sharper tuning curves (Fig. 5E).",
    "In CA3, information is greatest during early progression through the field, which corresponds to future locations, with a smaller peak during late progression, which corresponds to past locations.",
    "In contrast, past locations are more sharply tuned in CA1.",
    "Thus, different hippocampal subfields may differentially encode past and future positions across the theta cycle; we will return to this topic in the Discussion."
  ],
